===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms}}
{{wp|zh:,yue:,wuu:,en:Li (unit)}}
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*rwəʔ|t=village}} (STEDT, under PTB [https://stedt.berkeley.edu/~stedt-cgi/rootcanal.pl/etymon/2773 *r/g-wa]). Cognate with {{och-l|丘}} "hill, mound" & {{och-l|街}} "road crossing, street"; outsides Sinitic, cognate with {{cog|lus|khua||village}}, {{cog|cnh|khûa||village, cosmos}}, {{cog|my|ရွာ||village}}; {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} also proposes cognacy with {{cog|bo|ར་བ||fence, enclosure, wall, pen}} by pointing to a semantic parallel between {{cog|en|town}} and {{cog|de|Zaun||fence}}.

Alternatively, possibly related to {{zh-l|理}} "to divide into equal sections", yet Schuessler also noted that early Chinese villages were not systematically planned and platted.

